The paper presents a deep learning approach for object co-segmentation, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a CNN-based architecture, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves semantic feature extraction, mutual correlation, and mask generation, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
